result.name: Ah Lung Pakistan Halal Food

reviews.text: Doesn’t look like Pakistani restaurant at all. Looks like it’s being run by locals. Restaurant had the statues they pray to. Sell alcohol. No halal certification available. Although the lady verbally assured me it was all Muslim food. Curry was not good enough based in thick chunky onion sauce. Asked for medium hot, but was too spicy to eat. Very hard to find decent halal food In Hongkong. Any recommendations?

There are so many authentic curry restaurants and must really say this is probably the poorest and worst of them all in terms of hygiene, quality, taste, service, atmosphere and decoration. This is no where near any authentic Pakistan curry, who are they fooling.

Amazingly poor quality, really does not even deserve a 1, so dirty it is unbelievable. The food is bland and cold. Can't even really call what they serve as typical curries.

Will avoid this place at all costs, it is really appalling. Extremely bad experience eating here and it was plain awful.

The prices they charge are outrageous for what they serve. Very doubtful it is true Halal.
Opened for many years, famous for Pakistan curry. Curry beef brisket as I ordered was well tendered with heavy herb flavors. Thought it would be very spicy but not actually.
Need halal food in HK? Just come here
An inexpensive place for Pakistan curry.
